<TITLE> HC cancels new contempt law </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 24 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court has cancelled the Contempt of Court Ordinance 2008, declaring it illegal and unconstitutional. A High Court bench of justices ABM Khairul Haq and Md Abu Tariq gave the ruling Thursday on a writ petition by Supreme Court lawyers Md Shamsul Huq and Tajul Islam. The High Court on June 8 had issued a rule nisi on the government to explain why some sections of the new ordinance should not be declared unconstitutional and cancelled. Tajul Islam told bdnews24.com Thursday: "This verdict has established the supremacy of the constitution." Deputy attorney general Idris Khan said he had already prepared to file an immediate appeal against the verdict. The Contempt of Court Act 1926 was scrapped on May 25, to be replaced by the Contempt of Court Ordinance 2008. bdnew
